context: The word 'enamat' is the partitive form of 'rohkem' (more) in Estonian. It indicates a quantity that exceeds something or adds to what already exists. In English, it can be translated as 'more than', 'additional', or 'extra'. The word is used when talking about amounts or quantities that are greater than some reference point or when adding something extra to an existing amount.
